AGI - In Tuscany has been extended until 24 of Saturday 15 March the red alert for hydraulic risk of the main lattice, but limited to the lower basin of the Arno and Bisenzio and Ombrone pistoiese. The alert becomes orange, always until midnight, in Mugello and in the areas closest to Florence. Yellow code until midnight, and always for hydraulic risk of the main lattice, in the upper Valdarno.
The president of the Region, Eugenio Giani, has signed the request for declaration of state of national emergency after the wave of bad weather that hit Tuscany and in particular the provinces of Florence and Pisa. "We are addressing, together with local authorities, a very serious situation, with the great commitment of our Civil Protection and the precious support of the national one. But there is an important consideration to make - says Giani - the Arno system has worked,> is this the most significant element that we can highlight after hours of intense rainfall that particularly hit central Tuscany and the Arno basin. The work done in these years on the Arno has been decisive."
"The problematic situation that had come to be created in the lower course of the Arno - Giani explains that Sunday, March 16, along with the council member to civil protection Monia Monni, will meet the head of the National Department of Civil Protection Fabio Ciciliano - is&nbsp; it is effectively faced thanks to the filling of the expansion case of Roffia, 5 million cubic meters of water, that has immediately brought the benefits to prevent risks of Together with this, it was fundamental, yesterday at 15.50, the opening of the scolmatore in Pontedera, which guaranteed a constant flow of 500 cubic meters of water per second towards the sea bypassing Pisa. The flood of full arrived in lightened cities and the mighty loads of water >, while reaching two meters from the shoulders, did not cause tracimations".
"On the Florentine area - Giani explains again - is undoubtedly the great benefit that the lamination of the waters in the areas of expansion of Pizziconi, Levane and Restone, although not completely completed, has had on the Arno, lightened to the confluence with the Sieve, which could freely discharge in the main course. All the works propedeutic to the irregimentation of the Arno that are in progress, including the 13 bridles, have relieved the load and determined a fluidity that avoided the flooding of the great river".
&nbsp;
<h2>Critivity in Empoli
"It is evident - it says again - that there have been many damages in different municipalities, determined by the minor water courses and also from the Sieve, that has created a kind of own case of expansion in the stretch from the Medici Bridge of Pontasieve up to Dicomano, with damage to houses and enterprises on which we are already intervening. Problematica is still the area of Empoli, especially in Ponzano.> Numerous lands in the mountainous areas, which lead at this moment not to have direct road contact with Marradi and Palazzuolo on the Senio for the landslides on the Colla road. In the face of this situation there is still a very strong capacity for intervention of our Civil Protection, volunteers, mobile columns that are also coming from other regions."
&nbsp;
<h2>A Marradi 120 isolated persons, 29 evacuate</h2>
Meanwhile, the Municipality of Marradi informs that, following the intense rainfall of the last hours, the situation on the territory remains critical and constantly evolving. Currently, several roads are closed accessible only to help. The provincial roads Sp 74 and Sp 306 remain closed, with access only allowed to the rescue. "We are facing a very difficult emergency, made even more complex by the fact that our Municipality is cut off from the rest of Tuscany: at the moment we have about 120 isolated people and 29 evacuated people.> The means of the Municipality and the Metropolitan City are at work to free as soon as possible the isolated areas. We are in constant contact with the Civil Protection, firefighters and all the forces involved in relief to ensure security and assistance to the population - says mayor Tommaso Triberti - as municipal administration we invite all to pay maximum attention, to avoid unnecessary displacement and not to approach the water courses or areas at risk. I would like to thank the rescuers, volunteers and all those who, with great commitment, are working hard to deal with this situation." The railway traffic on the Florence-Faenza line remains suspended throughout the day on Saturday, March 15, for the damage caused by bad weather.&nbsp;
<h2><br> Monitoring on the north side of Santa Croce&nbsp;</h2>
The Santa Croce Opera today conducted an accurate monitoring of some stone elements of the northern loggia. It is "lion mouths" that once played the function of gargollas (final part of the gronde). The intervention was activated following the exceptional rains of these days, after the unfailing of one of the elements occurred. > On the basis of the monitoring it was decided, in a precautionary way, to remove three elements and to wrap the remaining lion mouths with the network. Visitors can regularly access the monumental complex. &nbsp;
<h2><br> Mayor of Pisa, "the full transit, we are optimistic"</h2>
&nbsp;"The fill of the full is transited also in the city section of the river - Michele Conti has explained - the night is passed without particular criticality. The work of the Scroller of Pontedera and the Expansion Case of Roffia allowed to maintain the Arno level under five meters. The best weather forecasts make us optimistic for the next few hours." So the mayor of Pisa Michele Conti, together with the head of the Civil Protection of the Municipality Luca Padroni, during the press conference at Palazzo Gambacorti to make an update on the situation of the full of the Arno in Pisa. "L'Arno - said again - is basically constant, we are at 4,8 m in Pisa, above the second level of guard fixed at 4,50 m. The models, data and weather forecast a gradual decrease in the next few hours, but very slow. The Arno is still guarded special."
"The alert is kept in red code because we are still above the second level of guard. In the afternoon there will be an update by the Civil Protection System of the Tuscany Region to understand what will be the evolution during the day. For now, a red code alert does not allow events, as in the case of today's match between Pisa and Mantua. We are working together with the preposed organs and with the ok of Lega B, Pisa and Mantova to try to make the contest Sunday afternoon. The progressive reopening of the bridges to the vehicular traffic has been arranged - the mayor has continued - while they will remain closed until new decision the Lungarni, at least until the early afternoon. The bridges Solferino, Aurelia, Vittoria and also the bridge of the Cep are reopening".&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>A Prato reopens cinemas, museums and sports facilities
The mayor of Prato, Ilaria Bugetti, together with the Civil Protection, made the point of the situation on the weather emergency. In the city there are still two families that have been evacuated: Both will stay in the hotel tonight. Case Coveri in Iolo can be reached at the moment only by means of adequate relief due to the flooding of the surrounding fields. To date, the closure of schools, public parks, cycle paths, cemeteries, markets and sports activities, private and public, outdoors and public entertainment venues remains in place. However, cinemas, museums, theatres and indoor sports facilities can be reopened, which had been held on Friday for precaution. &nbsp;
<h2><br> Mayor of Bologna, "damaging estimate for approximately €5 million"</h2>
The wave of bad weather that hit Bologna and the metropolitan territory caused damage to "about 5 million euros. They are not a few and are not a very dissimilar figure from what we had to allocate > already with urgent sums in the floods of 2023 and 2024". Thus the mayor of Bologna, Matteo Lepore, making the point after the last difficult hours lived by the Emilian capital of Romagna. A damage count that could increase exponentially, says Lepore, "especially for landslides and displacements." As for Bologna, there is concern for the "situation in Via dei Colli, closed road through the landslides", while in total there are 31 arteries that have reported problems. As for the closure of the schools on the occasion of the red weather alert, it was necessary "because this says the law", the first citizen moves. "As mayor I have the duty and the responsibility to make so that when there is a red alert of this gravity the city stops as much as possible, it reduces the mobility of people and puts in the field a plan of prevention, which we strengthened after the plan of May and October. We must treasure what has been, and we have done so by strengthening civil protection in the municipality and in the metropolitan city," he concludes.
<h2> <br> To Milan yellow alert until 17 March
The yellow weather alert (ordinary) on Milan was extended until Monday 17 March, emanating from the Functional Centre Monitoring Natural Risks of the Lombardy Region, for hydrogeological risk. The City Centre (COC) of Civil Protection will be active for monitoring and coordinating any interventions in the city.

